docs {
  # Clinical Co-Pilot — Bruno API Collection

  A runnable, source-free walkthrough of the Clinical Co-Pilot module's four
  HTTP surfaces. A grader can run this end-to-end WITHOUT reading module code.

  ## SYNTHETIC PATIENTS ONLY (OPEN-1)

  This collection is for the synthetic-data phase of the project. Point
  `synthetic_pid` at a SYNTHETIC patient only. Never run this against a
  database containing real Protected Health Information (PHI). PHI is only
  ever sent in POST bodies (never URLs), and a named redaction/BAA review is
  a hard gate before any real-PHI deployment (ARCHITECTURE.md §4, OPEN-1).

  ## Real endpoints (module pages)

  The doc's `/copilot/*` names are shorthand for these real module pages:

  - doc.php?pid=   → GET  the warm pre-visit synthesis page (session-auth)
  - chat.php       → POST one agent turn (session-auth + CSRF)
  - health.php     → GET  unauthenticated liveness (enabled + version)
  - ready.php      → GET  unauthenticated, redacted readiness (dep checks)

  ## Run order

  1. `Auth Bootstrap / Login` — logs in, captures the session cookie in the
     Bruno cookie jar (carried automatically by every later request).
  2. `Auth Bootstrap / Fetch CSRF Token` — GETs chat.php and extracts the
     `csrf_token_form` value into the `csrf_token` env var.
  3. `Endpoints / *` — health, ready, doc, and a chat turn.

  Select the `Local` environment first. Edit `base_url` and `synthetic_pid`
  to match your stack. The OpenEMR dev stack serves a self-signed TLS cert,
  so the CLI needs `--insecure` (see ops/README.md).
}
